header.gameNote: AIR FORCE RESERVE BASKETBALL HALL OF FAME TIP-OFF

article.description: Tyere Marshall had 25 points and 15 rebounds and Rider finished on a 25-0 run to beat Columbia 87-63 in the Hall of Fame Tip-Off on Saturday.
article.headline: Marshall scores 25 to lift Rider past Columbia 87-63
article.linkText: Marshall scores 25 to lift Rider past Columbia 87-63
article.story: UNCASVILLE, Conn. -- Tyere Marshall had 25 points and 15 rebounds and Rider finished on a 25-0 run to beat Columbia 87-63 in the Hall of Fame Tip-Off on Saturday. Stevie Jordan had 19 points and seven assists for Rider (3-2), which trailed 42-39 at halftime. Frederick Scott added 18 points and Dimencio Vaughn had 15. Mike Smith had 21 points and seven assists for the Lions (1-5). Jack Forrest added 19 points and Ike Nweke had seven rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
